## Agents

This project uses orchestrated agents from three sources. A detailed mapping
plus a "when do I use which?"-table appears in the orchestration section
below (when present) — Forge inserts it automatically when Superpowers or
curated awesome-agents are installed.

### Forge stack-specific agents

Spawn these via the Agent tool when PHP/SQLite/Forge-specific concerns are
in play:

- **frontend-reviewer** → `.claude/agents/frontend-reviewer.md`
  Spawn after any HTML/CSS/JS change. Evaluates Tailwind/DESIGN.md compliance,
  JS quality, REST API patterns.

- **db-reviewer** → `.claude/agents/db-reviewer.md`
  Spawn after any schema or query change. Evaluates SQLite schema (WAL mode,
  FK constraints), prepared statements, N+1 queries.

- **data-integrity-auditor** → `.claude/agents/data-integrity-auditor.md`
  Spawn automatically when fetching data from external APIs (Criteo, Meta,
  Google Ads, DV360, GA4). Run BEFORE any aggregation, calculation, or
  visualisation of external data. Also trigger when user says "dashboardet
  er klar", "vis data", "deploy rapport", "sanity check". Blocks all further
  progress on CRITICAL findings.

- **browser-tester** → `.claude/agents/browser-tester.md` (only if Chrome
  DevTools MCP is configured)
  E2E user-flow tests via Chrome DevTools Protocol.

- **mcp-health-check** → `.claude/agents/mcp-health-check.md` (only if any
  MCP is configured)
  Verifies MCP-server health: tool availability, auth, response format.

### Awesome curated agents (general domain expertise)

If `INSTALL_AGENTS=recommended` was selected during scaffold, your
`.claude/agents/` also contains generic specialists:

- **code-reviewer** — general code quality review (replaces Forge's old PHP-
  specific code-reviewer)
- **security-auditor** — OWASP, auth, secrets, CSRF/XSS
- **performance-engineer** — Web Vitals, bundle size, caching
- Plus type-specific: accessibility-tester, php-pro, sql-pro, api-designer,
  qa-expert, frontend-developer, javascript-pro (varies per project type)

Run `forge agents list` to see the full library.

